# Hook templates (from `hooks.json`)

Summarizes **156** hook files under paths containing **`/hooks/`** (see [`.agents/file-lists/hooks.json`](../file-lists/hooks.json)). Rules: **`rules-typescript-clean-code.mdc`** (only name with `use` if the function calls React or another hook), **`rules-bundle-react.mdc`**, **`rules-state-zustand.mdc`** where relevant.

## Inventory snapshot

| Fact | Typical value |
| --- | --- |
| Basename starts with `use` | ~96% |
| Extensions | `.ts` (~66%), `.tsx` (~28%); small `.scss` / `.js` |
| Path depth (median) | 7 segments |
| Common roots | `app/pages` (~66%), `app/features` & `app/hooks` (~16% each) |
| Largest slice | `app/pages/Result/...` (~59%) |

**Path examples:**

- `app/hooks/useBehaviorSubject.ts`
- `app/pages/Result/features/Filter/hooks/useFilterForm.ts`
- `app/features/CustomerEvaluation/hooks/useRatingInfoClickHandler.ts`

## Naming

- **`use` prefix** when the function uses at least one React hook or custom hook (project convention).
- **File name** matches the exported hook: `useFoo.ts` → `export const useFoo = ...` or `export default function useFoo`.

## Template — subscription / external observable

```typescript
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import type { BehaviorSubject } from "rxjs";

export const useBehaviorSubject = <T>(subject$: BehaviorSubject<T>): T => {
  const [value, setValue] = useState(subject$.value);

  useEffect(() => {
    const subscription = subject$.subscribe(setValue);
    return (): void => {
      subscription.unsubscribe();
    };
  }, []);

  return value;
};
```

## Template — hook returning elements or maps

- Prefer **pure data + small JSX factories** in the hook when building `Record<Enum, () => ReactElement>` maps; keep **map constants at module scope** when they do not close over props (see **`rules-typescript-clean-code.mdc`**).

## Template — `.tsx` hooks

- Use when the hook returns JSX or is tightly coupled to rendering; same naming and `use` rules apply.

